Control AT-3 in SP 800-53 requires organizations to provide role-based security and privacy training to personnel with organization-defined roles and responsibilities [1]. 

Specifically, this training must be provided:
* Before authorizing access to the system, information, or performing assigned duties, and at an organization-defined frequency thereafter [1];
* When required by system changes [1];
* With content updated at an organization-defined frequency and following organization-defined events [1]; and
* Incorporating lessons learned from internal or external security incidents or breaches [1].

Based on the provided excerpts, the requirements are as follows:

### SP 800-171 Revision 3 Requirement 3.1.8 (Unsuccessful Logon Attempts)
When the maximum number of consecutive invalid logon attempts is exceeded, requirement 3.1.8 requires organizations to automatically take one or more of the following selected actions:
* Lock the account or node for an organization-defined time period [1];
* Lock the account or node until released by an administrator [1];
* Delay the next logon prompt [1];
* Notify the system administrator [1]; or
* Take another action [1].

### SP 800-171 Revision 3 Requirement 3.2.1 (Literacy Training and Awareness)
Requirement 3.2.1 requires organizations to provide security literacy training to system users that covers:
* Initial training for new users and at an organization-defined frequency thereafter [9];
* Training when required by system changes or following organization-defined events [9]; and
* Training on recognizing and reporting indicators of insider threat, social engineering, and social mining [9].
